#: ./profiles/default/types/Complex.xml
msgid "A Complex is used to group fields together that are connected. Unlike normal fieldsets, a complex doesn't only group to enhance clarity and structure but to encapsulate related data or concepts. A Complex (including all contained fields, fieldsets, arrays, ...) can be dependent from the option of another field but a normal fieldset not."
msgstr "A Complex is used to group fields together that are connected. Unlike normal fieldsets, a complex doesn't only group to enhance clarity and structure but to encapsulate related data or concepts. A Complex (including all contained fields, fieldsets, arrays, ...) can be dependent from the option of another field but a normal fieldset not."

#: ./profiles/default/types/Field.xml
msgid "A Field represents a specific data entry point within a Form where users input information. Various types are possible, such as textline, number, email and more."
msgstr "A Field represents a specific data entry point within a Form where users input information. Various types are possible, such as textline, number, email and more."

#: ./profiles/default/types/Fieldset.xml
msgid "A Fieldset is used to logically group fields inside a Form, allowing users to organize related fields together. By encapsulating fields within a fieldset, users can enhance the clarity and structure of their questionnaires or forms. Fieldsets provide a means to categorize and visually organize fields, improving the usability."
msgstr "A Fieldset is used to logically group fields inside a Form, allowing users to organize related fields together. By encapsulating fields within a fieldset, users can enhance the clarity and structure of their questionnaires or forms. Fieldsets provide a means to categorize and visually organize fields, improving the usability."

#: ./content/field.py:159
msgid "A Placeholder is only possible if the answer type is one of the following: Textline, Textarea, Password, Telephone, URL, Email."
msgstr "A Placeholder is only possible if the answer type is one of the following: Textline, Textarea, Password, Telephone, URL, Email."

#: ./profiles/default/types/SelectionField.xml
msgid "A SelectionField offers users a range of options to choose from within a Form. These options consist of predefined values such as radio buttons, checkboxes, or dropdown lists. The type defines wether single or multiple selections are possible."
msgstr "A SelectionField offers users a range of options to choose from within a Form. These options consist of predefined values such as radio buttons, checkboxes, or dropdown lists. The type defines wether single or multiple selections are possible."

