#: ./profiles/default/types/Array.xml
msgid "An Array is a structured element that allows the repeated entry of related information by providing a template for a set of fields. It allows users to dynamically add additional sets of the same fields as needed. Arrays are particularly useful for capturing repetitive data entries, such as multiple contact or items in a list. An Array can be dependent from another field."
msgstr "An Array is a structured element that allows the repeated entry of related information by providing a template for a set of fields. It allows users to dynamically add additional sets of the same fields as needed. Arrays are particularly useful for capturing repetitive data entries, such as multiple contact or items in a list. An Array can be dependent from another field."

#: ./profiles/default/types/Option.xml
msgid "An Option represents a specific choice available to users within a Form. Options define the predefined values that users can select from, such as specific items, categories, or responses."
msgstr "An Option represents a specific choice available to users within a Form. Options define the predefined values that users can select from, such as specific items, categories, or responses."

#: ./profiles/default/types/OptionList.xml
msgid "An OptionList represents a collection of predefined choices available to users within a Form. OptionLists define the predefined values that users can select from, such as specific items, categories, or responses."
msgstr ""

